<paragraph role="heading" id="hd_id3151384" xml-lang="en-US" level="1" l10n="C"><link href="text/scalc/01/03080000.xhp" name="Value Highlighting">Value Highlighting</link></paragraph>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id3154366" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="U" oldref="2"><ahelp hid=".uno:ViewValueHighlighting">Highlights numerical values in your sheet.</ahelp></paragraph>
</section>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id3125863" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="U" oldref="5">To remove the highlighting, unmark the menu entry.</paragraph>
<section id="howtoget">
  <embed href="text/scalc/00/00000403.xhp#awehe"/>
</section>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id3145785" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="U" oldref="4">Text cells are formatted in black, number cells in blue, and all other types of cells, such as formulas, logical values, and dates, are formatted in green.</paragraph>
<paragraph role="warning" id="par_id3153188" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="U" oldref="3">If this function is active, colors that you define in the document will not be displayed. When you deactivate the function, the user-defined colors are displayed again.</paragraph>
